'active_lock_reason': None, 'body': 'Dear all,

No errors where found in the running of this worker but our prisma scanning tools revealed that libnetty has several vulnerabilities:

[
{"id":"CVE-2019-20445","packageName":"io.netty_netty-codec-http"},
{"id":"CVE-2019-20445","packageName":"io.netty_netty-codec"},
{"id":"CVE-2019-20444","packageName":"io.netty_netty-codec"},
{"id":"CVE-2019-20444","packageName":"io.netty_netty-codec-http"},
{"id":"CVE-2021-37137","packageName":"io.netty_netty-codec"},
{"id":"CVE-2021-37136","packageName":"io.netty_netty-codec"},
{"id":"CVE-2020-11612","packageName":"io.netty_netty-codec"},
{"id":"CVE-2019-16869","packageName":"io.netty_netty-codec"}
]
We think these are related to:
`
		<dependency>
			<groupId>io.grpc</groupId>
			<artifactId>grpc-netty-shaded</artifactId>
			<version>1.20.0</version>
		</dependency>
`
Which is a very old version of this dependency.

These were found when scanning https://github.com/Azure/azure-functions-docker that is used for our custom java function. Some of these findings are critical and need to be fixed in order for us to go to production with this product.

'author_association': 'NONE', 'active_lock_reason': None, 'body': 'Dear all,

No errors where found in the running of this worker but our prisma scanning tools revealed that libnetty has several vulnerabilities:

[
{"id":"CVE-2019-20445","packageName":"io.netty_netty-codec-http"},
{"id":"CVE-2019-20445","packageName":"io.netty_netty-codec"},
{"id":"CVE-2019-20444","packageName":"io.netty_netty-codec"},
{"id":"CVE-2019-20444","packageName":"io.netty_netty-codec-http"},
{"id":"CVE-2021-37137","packageName":"io.netty_netty-codec"},
{"id":"CVE-2021-37136","packageName":"io.netty_netty-codec"},
{"id":"CVE-2020-11612","packageName":"io.netty_netty-codec"},
{"id":"CVE-2019-16869","packageName":"io.netty_netty-codec"}
]
We think these are related to:
`
		<dependency>
			<groupId>io.grpc</groupId>
			<artifactId>grpc-netty-shaded</artifactId>
			<version>1.20.0</version>
		</dependency>
`
Which is a very old version of this dependency.

These were found when scanning https://github.com/Azure/azure-functions-docker that is used for our custom java function. Some of these findings are critical and need to be fixed in order for us to go to production with this product.

The Java worker team is working on a prototype where an Application Insights (AI) agent is deployed along side the Java worker
to handle telemetry and logging to AI. Depending on the SKU and environment variables, the AI agent should be used. 

Currently using a single profile environment to configure the usage of app insights agent.
We need to make changes in the host and create profiles according to these requirements:
| SKU | APPLICATIONINSIGHTS_ENABLE_AGENT | Expected Behavior | Default Behavior |
| --- | -------------------------------- | ----------------- | ---------------- |
| Consumption / pools  | true  | Start process with App Insights agent AND send data to App Insights | |
| Consumption / pools  | false | Start process with App Insights agent AND don't send data to App Insights |  |
| Dedicated / no pools | true  | Start process with App Insights agent AND send data to App Insights | |
| Dedicated / no pools | false | Start process without App Insights agent |  |

In simpler words for the customer, irrespective of SKU:
- Set `APPLICATIONINSIGHTS_ENABLE_AGENT=true`, enable app insights logs
- Set `APPLICATIONINSIGHTS_ENABLE_AGENT=false`, disable app insights logs
- Option to opt out if consumption


Sample `worker.config.json`
``` json 
{
    "description": {
        "language": "java",
        "extensions": [".jar"],
        "defaultExecutablePath": "%JAVA_HOME%/bin/java",
        "defaultWorkerPath": "azure-functions-java-worker.jar",
        "arguments": ["-XX:+TieredCompilation -XX:TieredStopAtLevel=1 -noverify -Djava.net.preferIPv4Stack=true -jar", "%JAVA_OPTS%", "%AZURE_FUNCTIONS_MESH_JAVA_OPTS%"]
    },
    "profiles": {
        "applicationInsightsAgentEnvironment": {
            "arguments": ["-XX:+TieredCompilation -XX:TieredStopAtLevel=1 -noverify -Djava.net.preferIPv4Stack=true -javaagent:agent/applicationinsights-agent.jar -DLazySetOptIn=false -jar", "%JAVA_OPTS%", "%AZURE_FUNCTIONS_MESH_JAVA_OPTS%"]
        }
    }
}
```

### Issue describing the changes in this PR

add logic to handle break change when customer using old java library and maven plugin where worker using restructured library. Add logics to handle this and avoid the break change.

### Issue describing the changes in this PR

add logic to handle break change when customer using old java library and maven plugin where worker using restructured library. Add logics to handle this and avoid the break change.
